      "references": "[Er77c] Erd\\H{o}s, Paul, Problems and results on combinatorial number theory. III. Number theory day (Proc. Conf., Rockefeller Univ.,\nNew York, 1976) (1977), 43-72.\n \n [Er80] Erd\\H{o}s, Paul, A survey of problems in combinatorial number theory. Ann. Discrete Math. (1980), 89-115.",
      "remarks": "In \\cite{Er80} he claims he 'did not state [this] quite correctly' in \\cite{Er77c}. The problem in \\cite{Er77c} which Erd\\H{o}s is presumably referring to states that if $n<q_1<\\cdots<q_k\\leq m$ is the set of primes in $(n,m]$ then\\[\\sum \\frac{1}{q_i-n}< \\sum_{p<m-n}\\frac{1}{p}+O(1).\\]See also [460] and [950]."
    },
